# Semantic Roles

Maps palette colors to functional roles in the color system.

## Background Hierarchy

| Role | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `base` | Primary background for main content areas |
| `mantle` | Slightly darker background for panels, sidebars |
| `crust` | Darkest background, used for extreme depth |

## Surface Hierarchy

| Role | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `surface0` | Lowest elevation, cards, inputs |
| `surface1` | Mid elevation, popovers, menus |
| `surface2` | Highest elevation, modals, dropdowns |

## Overlay Hierarchy

| Role | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `overlay0` | Tooltips, hints |
| `overlay1` | Multi-selection, secondary highlights |
| `overlay2` | Primary selection, focus rings |

## Text Hierarchy

| Role | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `text` | Primary body text |
| `subtext1` | Secondary text, labels |
| `subtext0` | Tertiary text, placeholders |

## Accent Colors

| Role | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `accent` | Primary interactive elements, links |
| `accent.hover` | Hover state for accent elements |

## Status Colors

| Role | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `success` | Positive actions, completed states |
| `warning` | Caution, potential issues |
| `error` | Destructive actions, failures |
| `info` | Neutral information |

## Border Roles

| Role | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `border` | Default borders |
| `border.focused` | Focus rings |
| `border.selected` | Selected state borders |
| `border.disabled` | Disabled element borders |